    "Liquidity providers on DEXs must balance potential adverse selection with fee income, raising questions about their strategies and returns (Lehar & Parlour, 2021).",
    "Quantifying the returns of liquidity providers is another topic that has received much attention in the literature (e.g., Aigner & Dhaliwal, 2021; Bergault et al., 2023; Khakhar & Chen, 2022; Milionis et al., 2023b).",
    "Among other things, liquidity provision on DEXs has been found to be influenced by other liquidity providers (Aoyagi, 2020) and other markets (e.g., CEXs) (Aoyagi & Ito, 2021).",
    "However, it remains to be clarified to what extent providing liquidity on DEXs is advantageous compared to providing liquidity on CEXs or not providing liquidity at all.",
    "For this reason, there are already approaches to measure the returns of liquidity providers on DEXs (e.g., Milionis et al., 2023c)."
